title: Time Manipulation part 1
description: See what time it is for me and for you.  View the times in your system default, 12 hour format or 24 hour format.

title: Time Manipulation part 2
description: Part 1 showed us the time for me and you the user, part 2 brings in the ability to chose any location and see all 3.  There are 38 total time zones in all.

title: Time Manipulation part 3
description: Taking the elements of part 1 and 2 we now add the ability to see my time, your time, and 3rd time but now lets see if it changes based on Day Light Savings Observation.  Not all countries or even time zones observe this find out which ones do.

title: Time Manipulation part 4 (Final?)
description: Adding to parts 1-3 did you know that those that observe Day Light Savings don't do so at the same time?  This project will have some added features to show you not only the differences but with luck when they change

title: Business Card Organizer
description: As a business owner I am always getting new contacts and sometimes they come in the form of a business card.  So this project will be a way to not only upload a picture of the business card but enter the information into a database (manually) and have it organized in any way the user feels is best, This will also have areas where you can have or keep an organized list of not just the business cards but websites.
notes: Might add shareability to this, or enable following.  As in the end this will need a database it will be external but will have a sample json file of data to show idea. The link side this might be similar to project 18

title: Veteran Family Resource
description: As a Veteran I know more about the benefits that I am entitled too than my non-Veteran spouse.  This is a problem.  If something happened to me he would not know where to look or what I am entitled too so this will be a project where the Veteran signs up and provides contacts that are able to also create an account and view important information not just about the Veteran but also the benefits.
notes: This might take some time and may have this one a group project or maybe a hack-a-thon event.  Would like to have some sort of dummy version for inside this app.
